article.headline: Cornell 79, Harvard 77
article.story: ITHACA, N.Y. (AP) -- Jason Hartford made a layup with two seconds left to lead Cornell to a 79-77 victory over Harvard in Ivy League play. Cornell trailed 68-61 with 5:13 left but got two late three-pointers from Lenny Collins, including one with 36 seconds left to tie the score at 74. Collins led Cornell (9-11, 4-2 IL) with 20 points. Adam Gore added 15. Matt Stehle led Harvard (12-7, 4-2) with 27 points and 12 rebounds before fouling out. Jim Goffredo added 20 points. Harvard went 27 of 29 from the free-throw line.
